page.title: 10BIOGRAPHY
page.content: MR PARKS,BORN IN 1910,HAS LIVED IN BARNHORN COTTAGE ALL HIS LIFE.THE HOUSE WAS ORIGONALLY HIS GREAT GREAT GRANDFATHERS AND IS 600 YEARS OLD.IT HAS VERY SMALL ROOMS AND LOW WINDOWS; THE CEILING HAS EXPOSED BEAMS.THE ANTIQUE FURNISHINGS ARE FAMILY HEIRLOOMS.HE USED TO BE A MARSH LOOKER AND HAS STUFFED BIRDS THAT HE SHOT WHEN LOOKERING.HE HAS A PET FERRET AND A BUDGERIGAR.HE HAS A COLLECTION OF OLD FARMING AND FISHING TOOLS,SUCH AS A SLUBBER-A METAL EDGED WOODEN SPADE FOR GETTING MUD OUT OF DITCHES,A 3 PRONGED EEL SHEAR FOR CATCHING EELS,A WICK TRIMMER AND A WIMBRILL.HE MAKES FOR FISHING AND ALSO HAMMOCKS.HIS OWN HAMMOCK IS ATTACHED TO A TREE HE GREW FROM AN APPLE PIP.ANOTHER HOBBY IS BIRD WATCHING.HE HAS NEVER OWNED A CAR:THE ROAD USED TO BE A TRACK WITH HORSES AND CARTS,THE CARS SCARE BIRDS.
